metadata.name: Awaiting Yesterday (SoC: Apr) #45
metadata.description:
Awaiting Yesterday On A Foggy Morning (SoC: Apr)

This is the memory of my childhood hometown,
mountains, trees, high sky and wet air, 
all of them are mixed in a silence and foggy morning, 
only birds fly out of woods.

--------------------------

This is also the third work of a larger portfolio of work 'State of Coherence' (SoC) which explores and describes the coherence of people, cultures and the objective world.

--------------------------

This is a generation artwork made by pure code.
In live mode, press 's' or 'S' to save a high resolution png.

Please be patient with drawing process (it'll take about 15s in my computer).
Enjoy~

Endlessworld
April, 2023

metadata.name: Parametric Decoy #81
metadata.description:
The project started with the discovery of an unusual shape. Draw two parallel sine arcs and connect their opposite points. That's how you get one slice of Parametric Decoy. The shape may appear in its different phases. Sometimes elegant, sometimes awkward. Sometimes broken, sometimes symmetrical. Only connectivity stays the same.

Features:
- size: small, medium, large
- color: *several options*
- background: transparent, halftone, cutout
- distorted: no, maybe*, twisted, displaced, yes**

* "maybe" means I'm not quite sure if distortion affects visible part of the shape
** "yes" means combination of "twisted" and "displaced"

Press S to save. To download in custom size (ex. 2000px width), add &size=2000 to url, reload and press S.

Made with p5js, inspired by pop-art collages and my own geometric sketches

metadata.name: Causality #68
metadata.description:
A response to the phenomenon of cause and effect. 

We think ourselves to be smart creatures for we have the ability to think, make decisions and communicate. And yet, we also often have to face the consequences of our past actions as we might have been short sighted in our purview in the past, maybe just as we might be even now. And we shall no not unless the future arrives. And to make matters a tiny bit more complex, my decisions might affect your reality and your decision may affect mine. 

We all understand causality, just like we understand Newton's third law of motion. The problem isn't in our understanding but in the limits we try to impose on it. For example, a person who doesn't wish to be short sighted will think of the future. But what does that mean? How exactly far out into the future should or even could a person think of? For you can always add another day to that same number hence making it quite the wicked problem. 

Causality ehh! A generative artwork made in cables.gl.

Press '1,2,3,4,5' to increase the resolution
Press 's' in LIVE mode to save a screenshot

Jaalibandar 2022

metadata.name: Sabler : Serengeti #162
metadata.description:
'Sabler : Serengeti' is a special edition reissue of the original Sabler generator in a vibrant 'Serengeti' palette which was omitted from the original collection. 

Towards the end of the production of the original Sabler collection, the creative decision was made to reduce the number of palettes from the thirteen that had been created to a smaller number, in order to improve the cohesiveness of the collection overall. While 'Serengeti' remained one of the stronger palettes, it was ultimately excluded in favour of the 'Annaliese' palette, in homage to an Anni Albers tapestry that originally inspired the 'Sabler' collection. 

Here, the 'Serengeti' palette is provided as a companion piece to the original Sabler collection to give collectors the opportunity to pair their output with their existing collection if they choose.

Below follows an edited description for the original 'Sabler' collection:

'Sabler', an anagram of 'Albers', is a generative homage to the work of the Bauhaus textile artist Anni Albers.

The aesthetic of this piece and its proportions are guided by the Golden Ratio (1.618 : 1) and as such, each part of the composition relates in some way to its larger self.

As lines playfully extend and overlap one another from various grid segments, patterns appear, 'ghost' shadings emerge and complexity is implied even with the use of very simple elements.

There are no rarities or special features, other than for you to enjoy the unique qualities of your piece!

You can save a high resolution 3000px x 3000px PNG of your edition by pressing the 'S' key.

metadata.name: Finding My Way #225
metadata.description:
This piece can be thought as a reflection on the paths we follow while finding our way through life.

Some of us explore more paths, others, less. Often, we find ourselves where we had been before, and we have to start again. Sometimes we take bold steps, sometimes less bold ones. Some paths are filled with love, others, with blues. 
We grow up, and we broaden our paths, or narrow them. 

Or, you can think of this piece as just a bunch of lines, grown progressively using a process similar to Substrate (Jared Tarbell, 2003), modified with a vector field generated with trigonometric functions. 

Random features include the color palette, the number of lines, their width, the scaling of the vector field, and margins.

Some color palettes were inspired by the beautiful plotter works of Iskra Velitchkova.

Original artwork by Roberto Ranon aka Dobleganger aka Doble ¬∑ Made with p5.js ¬∑ Udine, 2021

metadata.name: Flume #135
metadata.description:
Flume are infinitely flowing digital bodies of water.
The flow of Flumes can range from slow and gentle, creating small ripples and eddies, to fast and turbulent, carving its way through the inner workings of your computer screen. 
The color, clarity, and viscosity of the water can also vary.

This is the culmination of my collection Flume, an exploration into On-Chain art on Ethereum, https://etherscan.io/address/0x1fa23513825f952afca07a603ac3f312ebee4ca9

These pieces were all created in p5js.

- Andrew

metadata.name: Mooncakes: Happy Mid Autumn Festival 2022 #3513
metadata.description:
To celebrate the Moon Festival with Mooncakes, we have created a quest to introduce everyone to fxhash. As part of that quest on mooncakes.fun, users are encouraged to mint this generative token.

This is a layered image composition using the Mooncakes site images on a 1920x1080 canvas. The image elements are randomly assigned position, scale, tint, and blur according to a ruleset which generates a Mid Autumn Festival scene made up of: Moon, Clouds, Stars, Lanterns, and Lotuses.

Special filters, shapes and colors are included as rare features, as well as a couple of surprises.

metadata.name: Tezos Goons #281
metadata.description:
"When Humanity is in need, the Tezos Goons appear to fight the evil and aid the world..."


Tezos Goons is a pixel art PFP project that was created by the Greek Tezos community as a contribution to the collective effort to provide help for people affected by the devastating earthquake in Turkey and Syria through the #TezQuakeAid initiative. More info on the initiative can be found at https://app.joyn.xyz/contest/-tezquakeaid-gallery-a93c16832314

100% of the primary sales will go straight to the multi-sig contract that has been set up by @tezquakeaid and any royalties accumulated till the end of #TezQuakeAid will also be sent to the same contract to be used for the same cause.

"Tezos Goons" is a collective effort of the Tezos Greece community (https://twitter.com/Tezos_Gr).

The artwork of the project was created by the community member @MrEvdilos (https://twitter.com/MrEvdilos)

and the technical part was implemented by @mtsirides1 (https://twitter.com/mtsirides1) using @PureSpider's template. We thank them all for their kind contributions and their voluntary efforts!


For the Project:

Each Tezos Goon is randomly generated and has 7 traits (Background, Weapons, Bodies, Clothing, Mouth, Eyes, Headtop) from a total of 130 different options.

Another 6 "Legendary" animated Goons will be minted as a separate collection on Objkt and 5 of them will be given away to Tezos Goons holders through a raffle. Each goon that you mint (and hold) is 1 entry in the raffle. The 6th Legendary Goon will be auctioned for the same cause (#TezQualeAid).

metadata.name: Enfold #8
metadata.description:
‚ÄúWe saw the first blossoms late that year, an anticipated promise from the tenacious, etiolated fingers we'd observed making their way through the unseasonable snow; a dirty snow. They represented hope, pushing through this gritty crust formed of equal parts ice and ash making an inevitable descent from the troposphere. We kidded ourselves it was the earth washing itself clean, erasing all evidence of what we'd done, though we knew in our secret hearts that no amount of rainfall, ironically, could save us from the flood.‚Äù

Enfold is a piece based around distance: distance from circles, distance from centres, distance from edges. Points, places and relationships between separate entities are combined and forced through curated palettes of bright and vivid colours, producing overlapping, elliptical and lens-shaped areas formed from emergent, convex arcs.

metadata.name: Skies and Lands #80
metadata.description:
Skies and Lands is a collection of generative art featuring a house as the protagonist in an endless array of distinct landscapes. Each piece in the collection showcases a unique representation of the house located in different lands, with varied and dramatic skies providing a captivating contrast. The combination of the static architecture with the constantly changing landscape creates a stunning and never-before-seen visual experience. "Skies and Lands" collection invites the viewer to explore new perspectives and to enjoy the beauty of architecture and nature together. A timeless work of art that will undoubtedly delight art and nature lovers alike.

Don't miss the chance to own a piece of this unique and captivating collection.
